3652/// @brief Static helpers for developers
3653class Helpers : base::StaticClass {
3654 public:
3655 /// @brief Shares logging repository (base::Storage)
3656 static inline void setStorage(base::type::StoragePointer storage) {
3657 ELPP = storage;
3658 }
3659 /// @return Main storage repository
3660 static inline base::type::StoragePointer storage() {
3661 return ELPP;
3662 }
3663 /// @brief Sets application arguments and figures out whats active for logging and whats not.
3664 static inline void setArgs(int argc, char** argv) {
3665 ELPP->setApplicationArguments(argc, argv);
3666 }
3667 /// @copydoc setArgs(int argc, char** argv)
3668 static inline void setArgs(int argc, const char** argv) {
3669 ELPP->setApplicationArguments(argc, const_cast<char**>(argv));
3670 }
3671 /// @brief Sets thread name for current thread. Requires std::thread
3672 static inline void setThreadName(const std::string& name) {
3673 ELPP->setThreadName(name);
3674 }
3675 static inline std::string getThreadName() {
3676 return ELPP->getThreadName(base::threading::getCurrentThreadId());
3677 }
3678#if defined(ELPP_FEATURE_ALL) || defined(ELPP_FEATURE_CRASH_LOG)
3679 /// @brief Overrides default crash handler and installs custom handler.
3680 /// @param crashHandler A functor with no return type that takes single int argument.
3681 /// Handler is a typedef with specification: void (*Handler)(int)
3682 static inline void setCrashHandler(const el::base::debug::CrashHandler::Handler& crashHandler) {
3683 el::elCrashHandler.setHandler(crashHandler);
3684 }
3685 /// @brief Abort due to crash with signal in parameter
3686 /// @param sig Crash signal
3687 static void crashAbort(int sig, const char* sourceFile = "", unsigned int long line = 0);
3688 /// @brief Logs reason of crash as per sig
3689 /// @param sig Crash signal
3690 /// @param stackTraceIfAvailable Includes stack trace if available
3691 /// @param level Logging level
3692 /// @param logger Logger to use for logging
3693 static void logCrashReason(int sig, bool stackTraceIfAvailable = false,
3694 Level level = Level::Fatal, const char* logger = base::consts::kDefaultLoggerId);
3695#endif // defined(ELPP_FEATURE_ALL) || defined(ELPP_FEATURE_CRASH_LOG)
3696 /// @brief Installs pre rollout callback, this callback is triggered when log file is about to be rolled out
3697 /// (can be useful for backing up)
3698 static inline void installPreRollOutCallback(const PreRollOutCallback& callback) {
3699 ELPP->setPreRollOutCallback(callback);
3700 }
3701 /// @brief Uninstalls pre rollout callback
3702 static inline void uninstallPreRollOutCallback(void) {
3703 ELPP->unsetPreRollOutCallback();
3704 }
3705 /// @brief Installs post log dispatch callback, this callback is triggered when log is dispatched
3706 template <typename T>
3707 static inline bool installLogDispatchCallback(const std::string& id) {
3708 return ELPP->installLogDispatchCallback<T>(id);
3709 }
3710 /// @brief Uninstalls log dispatch callback
3711 template <typename T>
3712 static inline void uninstallLogDispatchCallback(const std::string& id) {
3713 ELPP->uninstallLogDispatchCallback<T>(id);
3714 }
3715 template <typename T>
3716 static inline T* logDispatchCallback(const std::string& id) {
3717 return ELPP->logDispatchCallback<T>(id);
3718 }
3719#if defined(ELPP_FEATURE_ALL) || defined(ELPP_FEATURE_PERFORMANCE_TRACKING)
3720 /// @brief Installs post performance tracking callback, this callback is triggered when performance tracking is finished
3721 template <typename T>
3722 static inline bool installPerformanceTrackingCallback(const std::string& id) {
3723 return ELPP->installPerformanceTrackingCallback<T>(id);
3724 }
3725 /// @brief Uninstalls post performance tracking handler
3726 template <typename T>
3727 static inline void uninstallPerformanceTrackingCallback(const std::string& id) {
3728 ELPP->uninstallPerformanceTrackingCallback<T>(id);
3729 }
3730 template <typename T>
3731 static inline T* performanceTrackingCallback(const std::string& id) {
3732 return ELPP->performanceTrackingCallback<T>(id);
3733 }
3734#endif // defined(ELPP_FEATURE_ALL) || defined(ELPP_FEATURE_PERFORMANCE_TRACKING)
3735 /// @brief Converts template to std::string - useful for loggable classes to log containers within log(std::ostream&) const
3736 template <typename T>
3737 static std::string convertTemplateToStdString(const T& templ) {
3738 el::Logger* logger =
3739 ELPP->registeredLoggers()->get(el::base::consts::kDefaultLoggerId);
3740 if (logger == nullptr) {
3741 return std::string();
3742 }
3743 base::MessageBuilder b;
3744 b.initialize(logger);
3745 logger->acquireLock();
3746 b << templ;
3747#if defined(ELPP_UNICODE)
3748 std::string s = std::string(logger->stream().str().begin(), logger->stream().str().end());
3749#else
3750 std::string s = logger->stream().str();
3751#endif // defined(ELPP_UNICODE)
3752 logger->stream().str(ELPP_LITERAL(""));
3753 logger->releaseLock();
3754 return s;
3755 }
3756 /// @brief Returns command line arguments (pointer) provided to easylogging++
3757 static inline const el::base::utils::CommandLineArgs* commandLineArgs(void) {
3758 return ELPP->commandLineArgs();
3759 }
3760 /// @brief Reserve space for custom format specifiers for performance
3761 /// @see std::vector::reserve
3762 static inline void reserveCustomFormatSpecifiers(std::size_t size) {
3763 ELPP->m_customFormatSpecifiers.reserve(size);
3764 }
3765 /// @brief Installs user defined format specifier and handler
3766 static inline void installCustomFormatSpecifier(const CustomFormatSpecifier& customFormatSpecifier) {
3767 ELPP->installCustomFormatSpecifier(customFormatSpecifier);
3768 }
3769 /// @brief Uninstalls user defined format specifier and handler
3770 static inline bool uninstallCustomFormatSpecifier(const char* formatSpecifier) {
3771 return ELPP->uninstallCustomFormatSpecifier(formatSpecifier);
3772 }
3773 /// @brief Returns true if custom format specifier is installed
3774 static inline bool hasCustomFormatSpecifier(const char* formatSpecifier) {
3775 return ELPP->hasCustomFormatSpecifier(formatSpecifier);
3776 }
3777 static inline void validateFileRolling(Logger* logger, Level level) {
3778 if (ELPP == nullptr || logger == nullptr) return;
3779 logger->m_typedConfigurations->validateFileRolling(level, ELPP->preRollOutCallback());
3780 }
3781};
3782/// @brief Static helpers to deal with loggers and their configurations
3783class Loggers : base::StaticClass {
3784 public:
3785 /// @brief Gets existing or registers new logger
3786 static Logger* getLogger(const std::string& identity, bool registerIfNotAvailable = true);
3787 /// @brief Changes default log builder for future loggers
3788 static void setDefaultLogBuilder(el::LogBuilderPtr& logBuilderPtr);
3789 /// @brief Installs logger registration callback, this callback is triggered when new logger is registered
3790 template <typename T>
3791 static inline bool installLoggerRegistrationCallback(const std::string& id) {
3792 return ELPP->registeredLoggers()->installLoggerRegistrationCallback<T>(id);
3793 }
3794 /// @brief Uninstalls log dispatch callback
3795 template <typename T>
3796 static inline void uninstallLoggerRegistrationCallback(const std::string& id) {
3797 ELPP->registeredLoggers()->uninstallLoggerRegistrationCallback<T>(id);
3798 }
3799 template <typename T>
3800 static inline T* loggerRegistrationCallback(const std::string& id) {
3801 return ELPP->registeredLoggers()->loggerRegistrationCallback<T>(id);
3802 }
3803 /// @brief Unregisters logger - use it only when you know what you are doing, you may unregister
3804 /// loggers initialized / used by third-party libs.
3805 static bool unregisterLogger(const std::string& identity);
3806 /// @brief Whether or not logger with id is registered
3807 static bool hasLogger(const std::string& identity);
3808 /// @brief Reconfigures specified logger with new configurations
3809 static Logger* reconfigureLogger(Logger* logger, const Configurations& configurations);
3810 /// @brief Reconfigures logger with new configurations after looking it up using identity
3811 static Logger* reconfigureLogger(const std::string& identity, const Configurations& configurations);
3812 /// @brief Reconfigures logger's single configuration
3813 static Logger* reconfigureLogger(const std::string& identity, ConfigurationType configurationType,
3814 const std::string& value);
3815 /// @brief Reconfigures all the existing loggers with new configurations
3816 static void reconfigureAllLoggers(const Configurations& configurations);
3817 /// @brief Reconfigures single configuration for all the loggers
3818 static inline void reconfigureAllLoggers(ConfigurationType configurationType, const std::string& value) {
3819 reconfigureAllLoggers(Level::Global, configurationType, value);
3820 }
3821 /// @brief Reconfigures single configuration for all the loggers for specified level
3822 static void reconfigureAllLoggers(Level level, ConfigurationType configurationType,
3823 const std::string& value);
3824 /// @brief Sets default configurations. This configuration is used for future (and conditionally for existing) loggers
3825 static void setDefaultConfigurations(const Configurations& configurations,
3826 bool reconfigureExistingLoggers = false);
3827 /// @brief Returns current default
3828 static const Configurations* defaultConfigurations(void);
3829 /// @brief Returns log stream reference pointer if needed by user
3830 static const base::LogStreamsReferenceMapPtr logStreamsReference(void);
3831 /// @brief Default typed configuration based on existing defaultConf
3832 static base::TypedConfigurations defaultTypedConfigurations(void);
3833 /// @brief Populates all logger IDs in current repository.
3834 /// @param [out] targetList List of fill up.
3835 static std::vector<std::string>* populateAllLoggerIds(std::vector<std::string>* targetList);
3836 /// @brief Sets configurations from global configuration file.
3837 static void configureFromGlobal(const char* globalConfigurationFilePath);
3838 /// @brief Configures loggers using command line arg. Ensure you have already set command line args,
3839 /// @return False if invalid argument or argument with no value provided, true if attempted to configure logger.
3840 /// If true is returned that does not mean it has been configured successfully, it only means that it
3841 /// has attempted to configure logger using configuration file provided in argument
3842 static bool configureFromArg(const char* argKey);
3843 /// @brief Flushes all loggers for all levels - Be careful if you dont know how many loggers are registered
3844 static void flushAll(void);
3845 /// @brief Adds logging flag used internally.
3846 static inline void addFlag(LoggingFlag flag) {
3847 ELPP->addFlag(flag);
3848 }
3849 /// @brief Removes logging flag used internally.
3850 static inline void removeFlag(LoggingFlag flag) {
3851 ELPP->removeFlag(flag);
3852 }
3853 /// @brief Determines whether or not certain flag is active
3854 static inline bool hasFlag(LoggingFlag flag) {
3855 return ELPP->hasFlag(flag);
3856 }
3857 /// @brief Adds flag and removes it when scope goes out
3858 class ScopedAddFlag {
3859 public:
3860 ScopedAddFlag(LoggingFlag flag) : m_flag(flag) {
3861 Loggers::addFlag(m_flag);
3862 }
3863 ~ScopedAddFlag(void) {
3864 Loggers::removeFlag(m_flag);
3865 }
3866 private:
3867 LoggingFlag m_flag;
3868 };
3869 /// @brief Removes flag and add it when scope goes out
3870 class ScopedRemoveFlag {
3871 public:
3872 ScopedRemoveFlag(LoggingFlag flag) : m_flag(flag) {
3873 Loggers::removeFlag(m_flag);
3874 }
3875 ~ScopedRemoveFlag(void) {
3876 Loggers::addFlag(m_flag);
3877 }
3878 private:
3879 LoggingFlag m_flag;
3880 };
3881 /// @brief Sets hierarchy for logging. Needs to enable logging flag (HierarchicalLogging)
3882 static void setLoggingLevel(Level level) {
3883 ELPP->setLoggingLevel(level);
3884 }
3885 /// @brief Sets verbose level on the fly
3886 static void setVerboseLevel(base::type::VerboseLevel level);
3887 /// @brief Gets current verbose level
3888 static base::type::VerboseLevel verboseLevel(void);
3889 /// @brief Sets vmodules as specified (on the fly)
3890 static void setVModules(const char* modules);
3891 /// @brief Clears vmodules
3892 static void clearVModules(void);
3893};

3917/// @brief Performance tracked scope. Performance gets written when goes out of scope using
3918/// 'performance' logger.
3919///
3920/// @detail Please note in order to check the performance at a certain time you can use obj->checkpoint();
3921/// @see el::base::PerformanceTracker
3922/// @see el::base::PerformanceTracker::checkpoint
3923// Note: Do not surround this definition with null macro because of obj instance
3924#define TIMED_SCOPE_IF(obj, blockname, condition) el::base::type::PerformanceTrackerPtr obj( condition ?
3925 new el::base::PerformanceTracker(blockname, ELPP_MIN_UNIT) : nullptr )
3926#define TIMED_SCOPE(obj, blockname) TIMED_SCOPE_IF(obj, blockname, true)
3927#define TIMED_BLOCK(obj, blockName) for (struct { int i; el::base::type::PerformanceTrackerPtr timer; } obj = { 0,
3928 el::base::type::PerformanceTrackerPtr(new el::base::PerformanceTracker(blockName, ELPP_MIN_UNIT)) }; obj.i < 1; ++obj.i)
3929/// @brief Performance tracked function. Performance gets written when goes out of scope using
3930/// 'performance' logger.
3931///
3932/// @detail Please note in order to check the performance at a certain time you can use obj->checkpoint();
3933/// @see el::base::PerformanceTracker
3934/// @see el::base::PerformanceTracker::checkpoint
3935#define TIMED_FUNC_IF(obj,condition) TIMED_SCOPE_IF(obj, ELPP_FUNC, condition)
3936#define TIMED_FUNC(obj) TIMED_SCOPE(obj, ELPP_FUNC)
3937#undef PERFORMANCE_CHECKPOINT
3938#undef PERFORMANCE_CHECKPOINT_WITH_ID
3939#define PERFORMANCE_CHECKPOINT(obj) obj->checkpoint(std::string(), __FILE__, __LINE__, ELPP_FUNC)
3940#define PERFORMANCE_CHECKPOINT_WITH_ID(obj, id) obj->checkpoint(id, __FILE__, __LINE__, ELPP_FUNC)

3945/// @brief Gets hit counter position for file/line, -1 if not registered yet
3946#define ELPP_COUNTER_POS (ELPP_COUNTER == nullptr ? -1 : ELPP_COUNTER->hitCounts())

4422// Check macros

4446#undef CHECK_STRCASENE
4447#define CCHECK(condition, ...) CLOG_IF(!(condition), FATAL, __VA_ARGS__) << "Check failed: [" << #condition << "] "
4448#define CPCHECK(condition, ...) CPLOG_IF(!(condition), FATAL, __VA_ARGS__) << "Check failed: [" << #condition << "] "
4449#define CHECK(condition) CCHECK(condition, ELPP_CURR_FILE_LOGGER_ID)
4450#define PCHECK(condition) CPCHECK(condition, ELPP_CURR_FILE_LOGGER_ID)
4451#define CCHECK_EQ(a, b, ...) CCHECK(a == b, __VA_ARGS__)
4452#define CCHECK_NE(a, b, ...) CCHECK(a != b, __VA_ARGS__)
4453#define CCHECK_LT(a, b, ...) CCHECK(a < b, __VA_ARGS__)
4454#define CCHECK_GT(a, b, ...) CCHECK(a > b, __VA_ARGS__)
4455#define CCHECK_LE(a, b, ...) CCHECK(a <= b, __VA_ARGS__)
4456#define CCHECK_GE(a, b, ...) CCHECK(a >= b, __VA_ARGS__)
4457#define CCHECK_BOUNDS(val, min, max, ...) CCHECK(val >= min && val <= max, __VA_ARGS__)
4458#define CHECK_EQ(a, b) CCHECK_EQ(a, b, ELPP_CURR_FILE_LOGGER_ID)
4459#define CHECK_NE(a, b) CCHECK_NE(a, b, ELPP_CURR_FILE_LOGGER_ID)
4460#define CHECK_LT(a, b) CCHECK_LT(a, b, ELPP_CURR_FILE_LOGGER_ID)
4461#define CHECK_GT(a, b) CCHECK_GT(a, b, ELPP_CURR_FILE_LOGGER_ID)
4462#define CHECK_LE(a, b) CCHECK_LE(a, b, ELPP_CURR_FILE_LOGGER_ID)
4463#define CHECK_GE(a, b) CCHECK_GE(a, b, ELPP_CURR_FILE_LOGGER_ID)
4464#define CHECK_BOUNDS(val, min, max) CCHECK_BOUNDS(val, min, max, ELPP_CURR_FILE_LOGGER_ID)
4465#define CCHECK_NOTNULL(ptr, ...) CCHECK((ptr) != nullptr, __VA_ARGS__)
4466#define CCHECK_STREQ(str1, str2, ...) CLOG_IF(!el::base::utils::Str::cStringEq(str1, str2), FATAL, __VA_ARGS__) \
4467<<"Check failed: [" << #str1 << " == " << #str2 << "] "
